The paper focuses on using reinforcement learning to enable a robotic manipulator to interact with objects in unstructured environments, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of deep learning techniques for this task suggests that it could also fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves using depth camera inputs, which suggests that it could fall under computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper involves transferring policies learned in simulation to a real robot, which suggests that it could also fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
